# Ironman AI — Strava Training Coach System

Personal training data pipeline that fetches workout data from Strava and exposes it via a local API,
allowing Claude to read and analyse training sessions directly — without manual copy-paste.
Built for Ironman World Championship 2027 preparation.

## System Overview

The system fetches cycling and running sessions incrementally (only new since last sync),
pulls full watt and pace/HR streams per second for recent sessions,
and exposes the data through a local Flask server tunneled via Cloudflare.

**What Claude sees per session:**
- Date, type, duration, distance
- Avg watts | NP | % of FTP (cycling)
- Pace per km (running)
- Average HR and cadence
- Full watt or pace/HR profile broken into 1-minute blocks with zone distribution

## Repository Structure

```
Ironman/
├── Ironman_AI.py          # Single-file system — sync, server and tunnel
├── strava_config.json     # Credentials (not on GitHub — see setup)
├── strava_tokens.json     # Auto-generated (not on GitHub)
├── workouts.json          # Local data cache (not on GitHub)
├── cloudflared.exe        # Tunnel binary (not on GitHub)
├── .gitignore
└── README.md
```

## Required Setup

### Strava API

Go to [strava.com/settings/api](https://www.strava.com/settings/api) and create an application:

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Authorization Callback Domain | `localhost` |
| Scope required | `activity:read_all` |

### Configuration File

Create `strava_config.json` in the project folder (never committed):

```json
{
  "client_id": "YOUR_CLIENT_ID",
  "client_secret": "YOUR_CLIENT_SECRET"
}
```

### FTP

Update the `FTP` constant at the top of `Ironman_AI.py` after each monthly Half Monty test:

```python
FTP = 190  # Watts
```

### Cloudflare Tunnel

Download `cloudflared.exe` from [cloudflare/cloudflared releases](https://github.com/cloudflare/cloudflared/releases/latest)
and place it in the project folder. Required for Claude to fetch data via public URL.

## How to Run

```bash
pip install requests flask
python Ironman_AI.py
```

First run opens a browser for Strava OAuth login. Tokens are saved and auto-refreshed on subsequent runs.

Output when ready:

```
✅ Sync faerdig — 60 aktiviteter totalt
✅ Server korer
✅ Tunnel aaben

📋 Send til Claude: https://xxx.trycloudflare.com/workouts
```

## Endpoints

| Endpoint | Content |
|----------|---------|
| `/workouts` | Formatted sessions with watt/pace stream profiles |
| `/workouts/raw` | Raw JSON |
| `/summary/week` | Weekly volume per discipline |
| `/summary/month` | Monthly volume per discipline |

## Dependencies

```
pip install requests flask
```

## Data & Privacy

No training data is stored in this repository. All local files containing personal data
(`strava_tokens.json`, `workouts.json`, `strava_config.json`) are listed in `.gitignore`.

Strava API access is governed by [Strava's API Agreement](https://www.strava.com/legal/api).
